Cut the @tenderstem broccoli{150%g} in half widthways. Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g}. Halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Zest the @lemon{1/2}(zested). Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a @salt{pinch} on to boil for the pasta.

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a #frying pan{} over high heat. Add the mushrooms and a pinch of salt and fry until browned, stirring occasionally, ~{5%minutes}.

> TIP: You don't want to overcrowd the pan as the mushrooms will sweat - do this in batches if you need to.

Turn the heat down to medium and add the onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5%minutes}.

Add the @tagliatelle{200%g} to the pan of boiling water. After ~{3%minutes}, add the broccoli to the same pan. Cook for a further ~{3-4%minutes}, until the broccoli and pasta are both cooked, then drain in a #colander{}.

Once the onion has softened, turn the heat to low. Add the @tomato ketchup{1%tbsp}, @paprika{1%tbsp}, @water{75%ml}, a squeeze of lemon juice, a pinch of lemon zest and the @Worcester sauce{15%ml}. Stir and cook for a few minutes to thicken up. Add @salt and @pepper to taste. When there is only a little liquid left, add the @soured cream{150%g} and give everything a good stir.

  Toss the pasta and broccoli into the sauce (use whichever pan is larger to do this). Serve the pasta in #bowls{}. Enjoy!